Hynix Shareholders May Limit Foreign Bidders’ Votes, Daily Says

-- B y   S a n g i m   H a n
-- 
2011-08-07T10:24:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-07/hynix-shareholders-may-limit-foreign-bidders-votes-daily-says.html
Hynix Semiconductor Inc. (000660)  shareholders
may restrict voting rights of foreign investors who would team
up with Korean companies, when they select a successful bidder
for their controlling stake, Korea Economic Daily said.  The shareholders including Korea Finance Corp. are
discussing about the protection of management when they select a
successful bidder out of SK Telecom Co. and STX Group, the
Korean-language newspaper said, citing a Korea Finance official
that it didn’t name.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sangim Han in Seoul at 
 sihan@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Cherian Thomas at 
 cthomas1@bloomberg.net  